&lt;p&gt;Are you planning a career in Orthopaedic scrub surgery?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-Do you want to be part of a surgical team with a range of specialities?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;-Are you ambitious and looking for a Trust where you can learn new skills?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Peterborough City Hospital is offering opportunities for band 5 Theatre Practitioners, RODP’s and RN’s.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position would suit newly qualified or those keen to add to their existing theatre knowledge and skills, with a commitment to developing and enhancing the quality of care provided in the operating theatre environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking highly motivated team workers who are professional, inspire others and embrace change and part of a multidisciplinary team. A flexible, can do attitude is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Peterborough City Hospital, we have a Main theatre suite which consists of 18 theatres specialities include, General surgery, Maxillo Facial, ENT, Urology, Gynae, Breast, Plastics, Ophthalmology, Orthopaedics, Trauma and two Obstetric Theatres. We cover an emergency 24hr service within the department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal enquiries or visits are welcomed by Helen Cousins Team Manager 01733677401&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note that this advert may close at any time and without&lt;br /&gt;notice. You are therefore advised to submit your application as soon as possible&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
